steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"921g7","text":"Add 5-10 mL of PBS. Gently swirl flask to rinse cells then remove PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f9b4g","text":"    - this removes serum proteins that might interfere with trypsin","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dlojn","text":"Add trypsin (0.05%, Gibco Cat. No. 25300054)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fgrog","text":"1 mL for T25","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"93c47","text":"2.5 mL for T75","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4qh75","text":"5 mL for T150","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"i93d","text":"Incubate flask at 37oC for 5-10 min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":20,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7p6lo","text":"- check the flask at 5 min by holding it up to the light, if cells fall off by themselves, culture is ready, if some remain stuck, continue incubating up to 10 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8h6np","text":"Add 4x volume of complete media into flask. Pipette gently up and down to collect dislodged cells. Transfer cells to a 15 mL conical tube. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"drcd0","text":"4 mL for T25","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"50npl","text":"10 mL for T75","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7irs3","text":"20 mL for T150","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"25v55","text":"Add appropriate volumes of complete media into a new flask. Label date, passage number and initials on flask. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6mt4g","text":"7 mL for T25","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"90arc","text":"13 mL for T75","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5uhl4","text":"30 mL for T150","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2ao9d","text":"After centrifuging, remove supernatant. Break up cell pellet by tapping the tube. Resuspend cells with 1-2 mL of complete media.
